# Modified based on si67021_lab13 code
def plot_cluster(X, y, class_labels, point_labels):
    num_labels = len(class_labels)

    x_min, x_max = X[:, 0].min() - 0.5, X[:, 0].max() + 0.5
    y_min, y_max = X[:, 1].min() - 0.5, X[:, 1].max() + 0.5

    color_array = ['#FFFF00', '#00AAFF', '#000000', '#FF00AA', '#FFAA00', '#FFAAFF', '#AAFF00', '#00FFAA', '#AA00FF', '#0000FF']
    cmap_bold = ListedColormap(color_array)
    bnorm = BoundaryNorm(np.arange(0, num_labels + 1, 1), ncolors=num_labels)
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 18))

    plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], s=65, c=y, cmap=cmap_bold, norm = bnorm, alpha = 0.40, lw = 1)

    for i, txt in enumerate(point_labels):
        offset_x = 0.01 if i % 2 == 0 else -0.01
        offset_y = 0.01 if i % 3 == 0 else -0.01
        if txt == 'Global':
            c = 'red'
        else:
            c = 'black'
        plt.text(X[i, 0] + offset_x, X[i, 1] + offset_y, txt, horizontalalignment='left', fontsize=10, color=c)

    plt.xlim(x_min, x_max)
    plt.ylim(y_min, y_max)

    h = []
    for c in range(0, num_labels):
        h.append(mpatches.Patch(color=color_array[c], label=class_labels[c]))
    plt.legend(handles=h)

    plt.title("Clustering Scatterplot")
    plt.xlabel("1st feature")
    plt.ylabel("2nd feature")

    plt.show()

def plot_labelled_scatter(data, x, y, region, continent):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))
    p1 = sns.scatterplot(data=data, x=x, y=y, hue=continent, palette='Set2')
    for line in range(0, data.shape[0]):
        if data[region][line] == 'Global':
            c = 'red'
        else:
            c = 'black'
        p1.text(data[x][line]+0.01, data[y][line], 
                data[region][line], horizontalalignment='left', 
                fontsize=6, color=c)
    p1.legend(fontsize=8, title_fontsize=9)
    plt.show()

K-means clustering¶

In [20]:
silhouette_scores = []
n_range = range(2, 11)

for n in n_range:
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=n, random_state=0)
    labels = model.fit_predict(X)
    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(X, labels)
    silhouette_scores.append(silhouette_avg)

optimal_n = n_range[np.argmax(silhouette_scores)]
max_silhouette_score = max(silhouette_scores)

print(f"Optimal number of clusters: {optimal_n}")
print(f"Maximum Silhouette Score: {max_silhouette_score}")

Optimal number of clusters: 2
Maximum Silhouette Score: 0.21075941301233284

Extensive Evaluation & Analysis¶

Silhouette Plot¶

In [52]:
tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=2, random_state=0)
X_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(X)

# Modified based on SI 618's code
label_points = False
for n in n_range:

    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2)
    fig.set_size_inches(18, 7)

    # 1st Subplot: Silhouette Plot
    
    # The silhouette coefficients' range is supposed to be [-1, 1]
    # This model's silhouette coefficients lie within [0, 1]
    ax1.set_xlim([0, 1])
    ax1.set_ylim([0, len(X_tsne) + (n + 1) * 10])

    model = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=n)
    labels = model.fit_predict(X_tsne)

    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(X_tsne, labels)
    print("For n_clusters =", n,
          "The average silhouette_score is :", silhouette_avg)

    # Compute the silhouette scores for each sample
    sample_silhouette_values = silhouette_samples(X_tsne, labels)

    y_lower = 10
    for i in range(n):
        # Aggregate the silhouette scores for samples belonging to cluster i, and sort them
        ith_cluster_silhouette_values = sample_silhouette_values[labels == i]

        ith_cluster_silhouette_values.sort()

        size_cluster_i = ith_cluster_silhouette_values.shape[0]
        y_upper = y_lower + size_cluster_i

        color = cm.nipy_spectral(float(i) / n)
        ax1.fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper),
                          0, ith_cluster_silhouette_values,
                          facecolor=color, edgecolor=color, alpha=0.7)

        # Label the silhouette plots with their cluster numbers at the middle
        ax1.text(-0.05, y_lower + 0.5 * size_cluster_i, str(i))

        # Compute the new y_lower for next plot
        y_lower = y_upper + 10  # 10 for the 0 samples

    ax1.set_title("Silhouette Plot For All Clusters")
    ax1.set_xlabel("Silhouette Coefficient Values")
    ax1.set_ylabel("Cluster Label")

    # The vertical line for average silhouette score of all the values
    ax1.axvline(x=silhouette_avg, color="red", linestyle="--")

    ax1.set_yticks([])
    ax1.set_xticks([-0.1, 0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1])

    # 2nd Subplot: Actual Clusters Formed
    colors = cm.nipy_spectral(labels.astype(float) / n)
    ax2.scatter(X_tsne[:, 0], X_tsne[:, 1], marker='o', s=30, lw=0, alpha=0.7,
                c=colors, edgecolor='k')

    if label_points:
        for i,v in enumerate(X_tsne):
            ax2.text(v[0],v[1],y.iloc[i][0],alpha=0.4)

    ax2.set_title("Clusters Visualizations")
    ax2.set_xlabel("t-SNE 1st component")
    ax2.set_ylabel("t-SNE 2nd component")

    plt.suptitle(("Silhouette analysis for Agglomerative Hierarchical Clustering with n_clusters = %d" % n),
                 fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    # plt.savefig('silhouette%02d.pdf' % n)
plt.show()

tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=2, random_state=0)
X_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(X)

# Modified based on SI 618's code
n = 8

fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2)
fig.set_size_inches(22, 10)

# 1st Subplot: Silhouette Plot

# The silhouette coefficients' range is supposed to be [-1, 1]
# This model's silhouette coefficients lie within [0, 1]
ax1.set_xlim([0, 1])
ax1.set_ylim([0, len(X_tsne) + (n + 1) * 10])

model = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=n)
labels = model.fit_predict(X_tsne)

silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(X_tsne, labels)
print("For n_clusters =", n,
        "The average silhouette_score is :", silhouette_avg)

# Compute the silhouette scores for each sample
sample_silhouette_values = silhouette_samples(X_tsne, labels)

y_lower = 10
for i in range(n):
    # Aggregate the silhouette scores for samples belonging to cluster i, and sort them
    ith_cluster_silhouette_values = sample_silhouette_values[labels == i]

    ith_cluster_silhouette_values.sort()

    size_cluster_i = ith_cluster_silhouette_values.shape[0]
    y_upper = y_lower + size_cluster_i

    color = cm.nipy_spectral(float(i) / n)
    ax1.fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper),
                        0, ith_cluster_silhouette_values,
                        facecolor=color, edgecolor=color, alpha=0.7)

    # Label the silhouette plots with their cluster numbers at the middle
    ax1.text(-0.05, y_lower + 0.5 * size_cluster_i, str(i))

    # Compute the new y_lower for next plot
    y_lower = y_upper + 10  # 10 for the 0 samples

ax1.set_title("Silhouette Plot For All Clusters")
ax1.set_xlabel("Silhouette Coefficient Values")
ax1.set_ylabel("Cluster Label")

# The vertical line for average silhouette score of all the values
ax1.axvline(x=silhouette_avg, color="red", linestyle="--")

ax1.set_yticks([])
ax1.set_xticks([-0.1, 0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1])

# 2nd Subplot: Actual Clusters Formed
colors = cm.nipy_spectral(labels.astype(float) / n)
ax2.scatter(X_tsne[:, 0], X_tsne[:, 1], marker='o', s=30, lw=0, alpha=0.7,
            c=colors, edgecolor='k')

for i, txt in enumerate(y):
    offset_x = 0.01 if i % 2 == 0 else -0.01
    offset_y = 0.01 if i % 3 == 0 else -0.01
    if txt == 'Global':
        c = 'red'
    else:
        c = 'black'
    plt.text(X_tsne[i, 0] + offset_x, X_tsne[i, 1] + offset_y, txt, horizontalalignment='left', fontsize=8, color=c)

ax2.set_title("Clusters Visualizations")
ax2.set_xlabel("t-SNE 1st component")
ax2.set_ylabel("t-SNE 2nd component")

plt.suptitle(("Silhouette Analysis for Agglomerative Hierarchical Clustering with n_clusters = %d" % n),
                fontsize=20, fontweight='bold')
# plt.savefig('silhouette%02d.pdf' % n)
plt.show()
